  <h2>Who We Are</h2>
  <p>We are the Pure Michigan Dub Coalition—a rogue sound system rising from the forests and warehouses of Grand Rapids. Rooted in the heavy traditions of Jamaican dub, UK free party culture, and Midwest grit, we build speakers, stack boxes, and bring bass to the hidden corners of Michigan.</p>

  <h2>Our Culture</h2>
  <p>This is DIY. This is illegal. This is sound system culture reclaimed by the people. No sponsors, no stage barriers, no rules—just deep frequencies, smoky air, and rhythms that echo through the pines.</p>

  <h2>Join Us</h2>
  <p>We throw guerrilla-style forest parties, powered by hand-built rigs, analog preamps, and love for the low-end. Our sessions are spiritual, sonic rituals—dub, steppers, roots, and experimental echo chambers for heads who feel the vibe.</p>

  <p>This isn’t a brand. It’s a coalition—a united front of sound warriors, dancers, and freaks who believe music is sacred and bass is healing.</p>

  <p>Let the dub guide you home.</p>
</main>

